<p>I'm having some trouble figuring out how to allow <code>xs:any</code> elements at the end of a complex type that has mandatory elements with a 1..1 cardinality.</p>  <p>Example:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xs:element name="ComplexElement" minOccurs="0"&gt;   &lt;xs:complexType&gt;     &lt;xs:sequence&gt;       &lt;xs:element name="Identifier" type="xs:string"  minOccurs="1"  maxOccurs="1"/&gt;        &lt;xs:element name="OtherAttribute" type="xs:integer" minOccurs="0" /&gt;       &lt;xs:any namespace="##any" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded" /&gt;      &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;   &lt;/xs:complexType&gt; &lt;/xs:element&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This will throw an error as the wild card would catch <code>Identifier</code>, which is only allowed once. I don't want to use <code>namespace="##other"</code> as the elements could be from the same namespace.</p>  <p>Any ideas how to address this?</p>